Because I hope we're good?

20:43.943 --> 20:49.010
Because things went weird a couple days ago, but now I'm here and you're here, like this, are we okay?

20:49.410 --> 20:57.920
And Samuel says to Agag, surely the bitterness of death is passed, but Samuel now responds in verse 33.

20:58.921 --> 21:05.789
And he says, as your sword has made women childless, so shall your mother be childless among women.

21:06.150 --> 21:12.097
And Samuel hued Agag to pieces before the Lord at Gilgal.

21:13.198 --> 21:16.562
Dang, don't get on his bad side.

21:17.282 --> 21:20.705
But see, here's Samuel who's like, Saul, you can focus on your image all you want.

21:20.845 --> 21:22.287
I'm gonna be obedient to God.

21:22.307 --> 21:27.392
And God said, this guy and all of the people associated with him because of their treachery had to go.

21:27.772 --> 21:30.114
And so sure enough, he's obedient to the Lord.

21:30.154 --> 21:38.202
And so that sets up now this downward spiral that we're gonna see with Saul that goes all the way on here to chapter 28.

21:38.262 --> 21:42.105
In fact, if you just look at chapter 17, it's a classic story.

21:42.125 --> 21:46.930
You may be familiar with it where the people of Israel gathered together on one side of Mount Elah,

21:47.202 --> 21:48.604
or the valley of Eli, rather.

21:48.624 --> 21:56.656
And on the other side come the Philistines and the Philistine giant Goliath comes down into the valley floor and says, is there any among you who will come and fight me?

21:57.477 --> 22:03.025
Now of all of the people of God, who was the person who was taller than everyone else in the land?

22:03.045 --> 22:06.230
And who was the person who could outbenchpress everyone else in the land?

22:06.490 --> 22:14.802
And who was the person who was supposedly the big strong tough guy king who when the champion from the other side came down, he should come, Saul.

22:15.490 --> 22:16.712
And yet, where's King Saul?

22:16.872 --> 22:24.602
Well, you find King Saul in chapter 17 hiding in his tent, and it's a little shepherd boy from Bethlehem who's going to come and deliver the people.

22:24.762 --> 22:25.564
We'll talk about him.

22:25.584 --> 22:26.465
His name is David.

22:26.885 --> 22:28.427
He's a man after God's own heart.

22:28.928 --> 22:32.973
And he comes down and takes out the giant that Saul should have taken out.

22:32.993 --> 22:35.597
Look at chapter 18, starting in verse 10 though.

22:38.180 --> 22:40.323
Saul is, he's in a bad place.

22:41.064 --> 22:45.330
And in chapter 18, verse 10, here's now David who's been anointed king.

22:45.634 --> 22:47.737
Saul knows his kingdom's taken from him.

22:48.338 --> 22:52.384
And it says that an evil spirit from God came mindily upon Saul.

22:52.464 --> 22:54.727
We'll talk about that theologically here in a couple of weeks.

22:55.468 --> 22:58.372
And so he raved in his house, so he's losing his mind.

22:59.293 --> 23:01.797
And David was playing the harp with his hand.

23:01.837 --> 23:02.678
They brought in David.

23:02.718 --> 23:05.362
And when David played music, it apparently calmed Saul down.

23:05.923 --> 23:09.408
And so David's there playing the harp in his hand as usual.

23:10.189 --> 23:12.332
And there's a spear in Saul's hand.

23:12.352 --> 23:13.714
So you can just kind of see,

23:14.242 --> 23:15.403
This is not gonna go well.

23:15.463 --> 23:16.784
I mean, Saul's on a bit of a bender.

23:17.065 --> 23:17.905
He's a little twisted.

23:17.966 --> 23:19.867
He's got a spear in his hand.

23:19.967 --> 23:22.149
Here's David, who's the one who's gonna take his throne.

23:22.169 --> 23:29.656
And so he, in verse 11 now, hurls the spear at David.

23:30.597 --> 23:32.880
And he said, I will pin David to the wall.

23:33.640 --> 23:37.744
But David escaped his presence twice.

23:38.585 --> 23:41.528
There's a lot of reasons you're gonna love and hate David.

23:42.408 --> 23:44.050
But this is one of my favorites.

23:44.194 --> 23:47.659
I mean, fool me once, shame on you, fool me twice, shame on me.

23:47.699 --> 23:51.846
I mean, the first time you throw a spear at me, I was kind of jacked, like, why would you do that?

23:52.527 --> 23:56.693
But then I go back and I'm dodging a second one, that's who David is.

23:56.733 --> 23:59.237
And so here's Saul trying to kill David.

23:59.498 --> 24:02.963
In chapter 22, David's gonna flee from Saul, they'll go visit priests.

24:03.804 --> 24:12.818
Saul hears about it, shows up, finds out that the priests gave David a little ziplock of some of the consecrated bread to go, and he kills all the priests.

24:13.538 --> 24:14.199
Just awful.

24:14.940 --> 24:24.613
And then in chapter 28, in verse five through seven, he's gonna now go, Samuel in this context is dead, Saul is freaking out.

24:25.554 --> 24:26.956
The Lord is not answering him.

24:27.016 --> 24:34.086
In fact, in verse six, it says he inquires of the Lord, but the Lord didn't answer him by dreams or the Urim or by the prophets.

24:34.727 --> 24:37.210
God would oftentimes speak in the Old Testament through dreams.

24:37.250 --> 24:43.058
The Urim was kind of a dice set that would be thrown to determine, kind of like casting lots.

24:43.266 --> 24:44.948
And even the prophets are silent.

24:45.068 --> 24:47.350
And Samuel, as I said in this context, is dead.

24:47.970 --> 24:51.153
And so he says, seek for me now a woman who's a medium.

24:51.854 --> 24:53.856
Some of your Bibles might call her a necromancer.

24:53.956 --> 24:57.459
It's literally someone who contacts somehow the dead.

24:57.860 --> 24:59.841
I mean, this is as demonic as the day is long.

25:00.642 --> 25:02.284
And I'm going to inquire of her.

25:02.704 --> 25:04.446
And so sure enough, they go find this gal.

25:04.506 --> 25:09.270
She brings Samuel back from the dead so Saul can have conversation with him.

25:09.290 --> 25:10.652
Really strange story.

25:11.192 --> 25:13.234
But Leviticus 1931 says,

25:13.986 --> 25:16.169
Do not turn to mediums or spirits.

25:16.690 --> 25:19.334
Do not seek them out or be defiled by them.

25:19.515 --> 25:20.677
I am the Lord your God.

25:20.957 --> 25:26.586
Point is, here's Saul in full blown panic and disobedience before the Lord.

25:26.606 --> 25:35.360
And then finally in chapter 31, he's mortally wounded on Mount Gilboa and says to his armor bearer, kill me and the guy's like, I'm not touching the Lord's anointed.

25:35.740 --> 25:41.810
So Saul falls on his own sword and all three of his sons die on Mount Gilboa with him.

25:41.922 --> 25:45.025
And so Saul is a king who finishes poorly.

25:45.105 --> 25:50.591
The question, though, that I want to ask and see if we can answer together is why then are these texts here?

25:51.552 --> 25:54.876
And I've said before that I think in some ways Saul is a cautionary tale.

25:55.376 --> 25:56.637
It's a really interesting book.

25:56.998 --> 25:58.479
I want to say the author is Gene Edwards.

25:58.499 --> 26:01.803
I need to look it up to confirm, but the book's called Tale of Three Kings.

26:02.504 --> 26:08.690
And the premise of the book, at least part of it, is that God put King Saul in King David's life to kill the King Saul in David.

26:09.442 --> 26:16.310
And so part of what happened in David's life being around King Saul is he saw the dark side of Saul and realized, you know what, I'm kinda like that too.

26:16.931 --> 26:24.020
And so I wonder if for us, if Saul's life like holding up a bit of a mirror is meant to show us, am I like him at all?

26:24.100 --> 26:27.484
Are there any things in his life that are similar to me?

26:28.205 --> 26:32.190
And there's a couple of things that maybe by way of observation, I would ask you to think about.

26:32.390 --> 26:39.218
One, Saul wanted the perks of the kingdom more than he wanted a relationship with the king.

26:40.322 --> 26:44.408
So Saul wanted the perks of the kingdom more than he wanted a relationship with the king.

26:44.428 --> 26:46.250
And I wonder if we do the same thing.

26:46.931 --> 26:53.481
Where we want the blessing of God based on proximity, based on association, based on affiliation.

26:53.501 --> 27:01.192
We want the blessings of God, we want the benefits of his kingdom, but we're not interested in a relationship with the king.

27:01.913 --> 27:03.214
Which are people who are religious.

27:04.116 --> 27:06.579
People just feel like, well, I mean, it's the right thing to do to go to church.

27:06.659 --> 27:08.562
Like good people go to church.

27:09.506 --> 27:10.307
Yes, but no.

27:10.507 --> 27:12.991
That's not what saves us.

27:13.772 --> 27:15.435
That's not what transforms us.

27:15.495 --> 27:17.157
That's not what sanctifies us.

27:17.598 --> 27:20.282
Proximity alone is not the answer.

27:20.602 --> 27:22.345
It's not about proximity or affiliation.

27:22.365 --> 27:23.727
People say, wow, I'm a Christian.

27:23.747 --> 27:24.608
I grew up in a Christian home.

27:24.648 --> 27:25.970
That's not the gospel.

27:26.911 --> 27:28.513
You can grow up in a Christian home.

27:28.533 --> 27:29.835
You can grow up in a church.

27:29.855 --> 27:35.083
You can participate in religious activities and never be reconciled to your God through Christ.

27:36.245 --> 27:37.266
You're religious.

27:37.538 --> 27:43.589
And you may look on the outside more moral than others who don't, but the goal isn't to be moral.

27:44.310 --> 27:46.194
The goal is to be reconciled to God.

27:46.555 --> 27:48.198
Morality is an afterthought.

27:48.298 --> 27:51.243
It's a byproduct of being reconciled to God.

27:51.704 --> 28:01.522
And Jesus is going to say that not everyone who says to me, Lord, Lord, we'll enter the kingdom of heaven, but the one who does the will of the Father, he will enter.

28:01.826 --> 28:08.436
And many will say to me on that day, Lord, Lord, why didn't we prophesy in your name and in your name cast out demons and in your name do many miracles?

28:08.456 --> 28:13.103
And he will say to them, I never knew you, depart from me, you who practice lawlessness.

28:13.704 --> 28:27.364
Is it possible for us to be around the things of God, to attend church, to be in a life group, to be in proximity to people that are godly people and not actually know Jesus ourself?

28:27.444 --> 28:28.946
And the answer of course is yes.

28:29.826 --> 28:32.829
And so when Jesus says, I am the way, I am the truth, I am the life.

28:33.269 --> 28:41.917
No one comes to the Father, but through me, don't miss the blessings of the kingdom or don't conflate the blessings of the kingdom with a reconciliation with your king.

28:42.798 --> 28:48.023
So if you are here today and you have never trusted in Jesus Christ, that's where new life begins.

28:48.984 --> 28:50.085
Something has to happen.

28:51.326 --> 28:53.548
You have to embrace the gospel of Jesus Christ.

28:54.009 --> 28:58.913
Then the messy process of life with God begins together, but you've got to embrace the gospel.

28:58.973 --> 28:59.634
Second,

28:59.874 --> 29:09.146
is it seems like Saul, he wanted the blessing of God, but without personal obedience to God.

29:10.027 --> 29:15.834
So he wanted God to bless him, but he wasn't willing to do the things required on his end.

29:15.854 --> 29:22.002
Equivalent would be this, I wonder if it's possible for us to say, God, would you bless my business?

29:23.074 --> 29:30.765
And yet we're out cooking the books or being dishonest with expense reports or not being candid with clients or ripping people off.

29:30.785 --> 29:31.667
God bless me.

29:31.687 --> 29:34.871
Now I'm gonna do what I'm doing over here, but God bless me.

29:35.692 --> 29:38.236
Is it possible to say, God, would you bless my marriage?

29:39.378 --> 29:43.504
And yet we're not willing to do the things that are required of us in our marriage.

29:44.165 --> 29:50.514
And we're just asking for God's blessing without our participation at all, where that one hits for me a little bit.

29:50.818 --> 29:55.923
Is there's a pattern that we're beginning to see around that's very concerning as it relates to marriages?

29:56.644 --> 30:05.813
Is we'll hear a lot of talk about she, her, if she'll change, or she'll change, or she'll change, and I'm looking at the guy going, time out.

30:06.494 --> 30:15.163
Last time I checked, you're the spiritual leader of your home, which means if you have a problem in your marriage, you have a problem in your marriage.

30:15.183 --> 30:18.546
Now, I'm not suggesting that it's 100% your fault,

30:18.658 --> 30:21.481
but it's certainly not 100% her fault.

30:21.501 --> 30:27.168
And the question is, what does it mean for a man to love his wife the way Christ loved the church?

30:27.849 --> 30:39.262
What does it mean for a man to, for a husband to live with his wife in an understanding way as with a weaker vessel for she's a woman and to treat her with honor as a fellow heir to the grace of life so that your prayers will not be hindered?

30:39.923 --> 30:45.970
And I hear a lot of people in marriages blaming the wife without taking responsibility as a man.

30:46.370 --> 30:58.169
But men, if you have a problem in your marriage, it is your problem and your responsibility to fight like mad and be obedient to everything God called you to be in that marriage.

30:58.770 --> 31:05.580
Anything less is to abdicate our responsibility as men and to offer our marriages to the whims of culture.

31:05.661 --> 31:06.362
God help us.

31:06.442 --> 31:07.824
No, no, we have a responsibility.

31:08.084 --> 31:14.194
So we can't say God bless my marriage if we're not willing to do what we're responsible to do on our end.

31:14.626 --> 31:18.850
And by the way, that first Peter passage says that our prayers are hindered if our marriage isn't okay.

31:19.170 --> 31:23.655
So don't come to me, fellas, and say, I'm doing great with the Lord, but boy, that wife.

31:25.577 --> 31:26.438
She's the problem.

31:26.518 --> 31:28.380
I said, no, I don't think that's the case.

31:28.640 --> 31:32.484
Because your relationship with God is intimately connected to your relationship with your wife.

31:32.784 --> 31:37.589
And we have to take responsibility for our marriages, men, and for our homes.

31:37.829 --> 31:38.870
That's a us issue.

31:39.390 --> 31:41.232
And so we've got to take that upon ourselves.

31:41.272 --> 31:42.994
And then I think with that also,

31:43.938 --> 31:58.962
It's easy for us to say, God, would you bless my family, for example, when we haven't had dinner as a family together at a table in weeks that we're doing life into go boxes in the back seat of our car, going from one thing to another.

31:59.262 --> 32:12.082
And if we're honest, I just wonder, are we offering our kids on the altar of athletic prowess and compromising what might be even more important, which is the development of their souls?

32:12.802 --> 32:13.843
I mean, no offense.

32:13.883 --> 32:16.386
You probably do have a future Olympian in your home.

32:18.269 --> 32:19.210
You probably do.

32:19.250 --> 32:31.285
And so you probably should be in every club this and every club that and you probably do need a trainer and you probably do need a nutritionist and you probably do because that person might be the best athlete we have ever seen.

32:32.646 --> 32:38.694
Or it could be that after high school they're never going to play anything ever again.

32:38.714 --> 32:42.098
And so what is it profit?

32:42.306 --> 32:47.511
A person to gain the whole world and forfeit their soul for what can they give an exchange?

32:47.531 --> 32:50.394
So maybe we had to shift our priorities.

32:50.434 --> 32:51.635
Finally, sorry, too convicting.

32:51.675 --> 32:52.516
I feel better, by the way.

32:52.576 --> 32:53.117
Should we move on?

32:55.259 --> 32:56.160
Finally, let me say this.

32:58.081 --> 32:58.682
Let me say this.

32:59.763 --> 33:09.112
Saul was so fixated on himself that as he's making bad decision after bad decision, he just refused to confess and repent.

33:10.273 --> 33:10.834
Yes.

33:11.074 --> 33:15.039
He said the words, but they feel different, don't they?

33:15.580 --> 33:16.581
They feel shallow.

33:17.623 --> 33:18.845
They feel performative.

33:19.525 --> 33:24.973
David is gonna say in Psalm 32, when I kept silent about my sin, my bones wasted away within me.

33:25.013 --> 33:29.980
The heavy hand of the Lord was upon me, but when I confessed my sin, he restored my soul.

33:30.320 --> 33:31.602
That feels different to me.

33:32.543 --> 33:34.686
And so I just wonder, is it possible for us?

33:35.247 --> 33:38.111
We make a bad decision and then we make another.

33:38.792 --> 33:40.594
By the way, the first one's the hardest to make.

33:41.346 --> 33:44.290
The second one comes easier, the third comes easier, the fourth and the fifth.

33:44.330 --> 33:48.635
Next thing you know, it's like the person that's like digging their own grave and they just keep digging.

33:48.656 --> 33:50.298
You're like, put the shovel down.

33:51.199 --> 33:52.060
Just stop.

33:52.721 --> 33:58.008
And instead of trying to justify everything, what if you just said, oh God, I have just blown it.

33:59.109 --> 34:00.711
God, search me, oh God, I know my heart.

34:00.751 --> 34:02.033
Try me, I know my anxious thoughts.

34:02.053 --> 34:04.276
See if there be any hurtful way in me.

34:04.316 --> 34:05.938
God, I confess my sin to you.

34:06.402 --> 34:12.691
And the scripture reminds us if we confess our sin he is faithful and just to forgive us of our sin and purify us from all unrighteousness.

34:12.791 --> 34:23.367
Not only when we confess and repent do we experience restoration with the king, but John is gonna tell us when we walk in the light as he is in the light, that's actually where we have fellowship together.

34:24.148 --> 34:31.459
And so the irony is by owning our stuff, reciprocal relationship is restored with others because we were honest.

34:32.340 --> 34:33.842
And if we're hiding our sin,

34:34.466 --> 34:43.757
If we're living in deception, if we're blaming everybody like Saul did around us, accept ourselves, then there's no relationship that can be had because you're not willing to own anything.

34:45.860 --> 34:47.622
You're not owning anything.

34:47.642 --> 34:52.207
You're not honest with anything, which means you're not interested in reciprocal relationship.

34:52.688 --> 35:01.238
You're interested in being right, or at least the perception of you being right, where there's just something so incredibly restorative.

35:01.539 --> 35:02.340
You just go, you know what?

35:02.600 --> 35:03.261
I'm so sorry.

35:03.441 --> 35:04.242
That's on me.

35:04.514 --> 35:05.877
I should not have done that.

35:05.897 --> 35:06.798
This is what I did.

35:06.818 --> 35:08.501
I want to ask your forgiveness.

35:08.582 --> 35:09.583
I want to repent of that.

35:09.704 --> 35:13.871
And then reconcile relationship, not just with God, but with others.

35:14.432 --> 35:24.050
And man, if we're not careful, Scripture reminds us the one who hardens their neck rather after much reproof will suddenly be broken beyond all remedy.

35:25.218 --> 35:30.023
This is something beautiful about learning how to confess and repent versus being stubborn and fighting.

35:30.103 --> 35:34.828
Saul is stubborn and fights his way all the way to falling on his own sword on Mount Gilboa.

35:35.549 --> 35:44.819
May it never be that we have that kind of hard heart, but instead could we be men and women who pursue now reconciliation with our God through confession and repentance.

35:44.859 --> 35:47.442
And in that reconciliation with one another, amen?

35:48.523 --> 35:50.145
Saul wanted the benefits of the kingdom.

35:50.205 --> 35:50.906
He didn't want the king.

35:51.687 --> 35:54.930
Saul wanted the blessings of God, but not personal obedience.

35:55.234 --> 36:01.001
And Saul went headlong into sin with no confession or repentance, and it led to destruction.

36:01.201 --> 36:03.423
And so Saul is a cautionary tale.

36:03.443 --> 36:09.891
And maybe by God's grace, God put King Saul in our lives to kill the King Saul that's in us.

36:10.431 --> 36:10.852
Let's pray.

36:11.512 --> 36:16.538
Father in heaven, what a gift to read the scriptures and to learn from those who have gone before.

36:16.598 --> 36:18.340
They are here for our instruction.

36:18.861 --> 36:20.743
And so for that we're grateful.

36:20.763 --> 36:23.506
And may we learn the lessons that we need to learn.

36:24.002 --> 36:27.068
from pages of the scriptures from long ago.

36:27.810 --> 36:37.408
That by your grace, we might enjoy relationship with you and life in your kingdom in the joy of repentance and reconciliation with our King.

36:38.330 --> 36:40.334
All of it, Father, for your glory and our good.

36:40.454 --> 36:42.138
And we'll thank you in your name.

36:42.158 --> 36:42.258
Amen.

